            <h1 class="hTitle">Hi,</h1>

            <div class="w3-section w3-justify">
                I am Peter, and this (2016) year at the age of 40 I became a Front-end Developer.
                A year and a half ago I started learning
                WEB programming from scratch. A couple of weeks ago I passed a 3-hour interview (15 minutes
                with an HR, 2 hours and a half with 2 front-end developers and 15 minutes with a manager),
                and as a result I got a job offer to join
                <a class="w3-pale-blue w3-btn" href="https://www.scnsoft.com" target="_blank">this</a> company
                as a Front-end developer of applications for mobile devices.
            </div>

            <div class="w3-container w3-justify w3-pale-yellow w3-leftbar w3-border-yellow w3-padding-large
            w3-margin-24">
                <p><i>To become a computer programmer it is not necessary to go to any courses or study at the University
                        or some school. There is everything in the internet for that. There's absolutely everything.</i>
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="w3-section w3-justify">
                Fot this one year and a half I learned such technologies as HTML, CSS, JavaScript,
                BackboneJS, RequireJS, Underscore, NodeJS, Express, MongoDB, Mongoose, Grunt, Less, Jade, Bootstrap,
                Git.
            </div>

            <div class="w3-section w3-justify">
                In short, this is Full-stack, i.e. for a year and a half I learned how to create static and dynamic
                web sites and single-page applications, writing both Front-end and Back-end scripts with vanilla
                JavaScript and such frameworks as BackboneJS, RequireJS. I learned how to
                code NodeJS server and MongoDB database.
            </div>

            <div id="factors" class="w3-section w3-justify">
                In my case such great efficiency of learning was due to the following factors:
            </div>

            <div class="w3-accordion w3-light-grey w3-margin-12">
